        {
          "scid": "thig5.4:1.0.3",
          "en": "4. Nanda's Vision"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig5.4:1.0.4",
          "en": "\"Sick, putrid, unclean: look, Nanda, at this physical heap. Through contemplation of the foul, develop your mind, make it one, well-centered."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig5.4:1.0.5",
          "en": "As this [your body], so that. As that, so this. It gives off a foul stench, the delight of fools.\""
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig5.4:1.0.6",
          "en": "Considering it thus, untiring, both day & night, I, with my own discernment dissecting it, saw."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig5.4:1.0.7",
          "en": "And as I, heedful, examined it aptly, this body — as it actually is — was seen inside & out."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig5.4:1.0.8",
          "en": "Then was I disenchanted with the body & dispassionate within: Heedful, detached, calmed was I. Unbound."
        }
      ],
